wiki.content: On “Feline”, Juice WRLD is criticizing and scaring his opposition. Throughout the track, Juice discusses topics such as their hardened mindsets, their weaponry, their sexual prowess, and their willingness to utilize violence in the event of confrontation. “Feline” was originally recorded in early 2018, during the sessions for Juice’s debut studio album Goodbye & Good Riddance, albeit in an unfinished state with an open verse. A completed version of the track was recorded later in 2018, during the sessions for Future and Juice WRLD’s collaborative mixtape WRLD on Drugs, with the open verse being filled by Atlanta rapper Lil Yachty. The original demo of this track was leaked in its entirety on November 3, 2019, and the demo featuring Lil Yachty was leaked on February 5, 2020. This version of the track was leaked in its entirety on November 22, 2021. A version with Trippie Redd & Polo G released on Fighting Demons in December 10, 2021. Read more on Last.fm.
